Liechtenstein Wants Swiss-Style Tax Pact With Germany, FAZ Says

-- B y   P a t r i c k   D o n a h u e
-- 
2011-06-07T07:41:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-07/liechtenstein-wants-swiss-style-tax-pact-with-germany-faz-says.html
Liechtenstein wants to pursue an
agreement with  Germany  along the lines of a withholding tax
being negotiated between Swiss and German authorities,
Liechtenstein Prime Minister Klaus Tschuetscher told the
 Frankfurter Allgemeine Zeitung .  The government in Vaduz would pursue an agreement with
Germany soon after negotiations with  Switzerland  are completed
in the coming month, Tschuetscher told the newspaper.  According to the German-Swiss agreement, Swiss authorities
will charge a withholding tax on assets held by German nationals
that would preserve a level of bank secrecy.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Patrick Donahue in Berlin at  at
 pdonahue1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Hertling at 
 jhertling@bloomberg.net  